{
  "stem": "7832.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They wouldn't allow-- they didn't allow me to go to their homes anymore.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't-- they were taking things from me to make me upset.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They-- they did all this, you know, showing me how-- how they don't like me anymore.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I don't know whether they were coached by their parents.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was in '39 and '40, '41.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And all this pressure I felt from different-- different.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So the Jewish children-- I, for one, was stuck to home, because I was so disappointed in-- in-- in the outside closeness with people, that I-- whatever I could do, I just did at home.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I used love to write, so I used to write poems and-- and-- and songs, and and all that stuff.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father's parents lived in-- we had a duplex house, so they lived on the other side of the house, and we celebrated Shabbat and all holidays together.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On a Friday, it was the busiest day of the week, because even my-- my mother's mother, which lived in the next town, used to come early Friday morning and woke everybody up at 5:00 in the morning and-- to bake challah and bread and rolls for the week.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "For the whole week, we did on Friday.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was eight years old, and I had to get up at 5 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was still going to school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Jewish children were not restricted from school yet.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she woke me up at 5 o'clock in the morning, and she taught me how to make matzo for the soup, and to braid the challah for Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was very angry with her, because I wanted to sleep at 5 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
